The paper focuses on the LRU cache, which is a data structure commonly used in computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also deals with the hit probability of the cache, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and probability theory (cs.PR). The paper also discusses the cache under stationary requests, which can be modeled as a dynamical system (cs.SY). The paper also establishes the rate of convergence, which involves mathematical analysis (cs.MA) and possibly control theory (cs.PF).
